label.value: ellipsoid body ventral tile

value.value: Ventralmost tile of the ellipsoid body, spanning both hemispheres (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: ellipsoid body lateral tile

value.value: Lateralmost tile of the ellipsoid body, there is one per hemisphere (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: ellipsoid body dorsolateral tile

value.value: Dorsolateral tile of the ellipsoid body, between the dorsal and lateral tiles, there is one per hemisphere (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: ellipsoid body ventrolateral tile

value.value: Ventrolateral tile of the ellipsoid body, between the ventral and lateral tiles, there is one per hemisphere (Wolff et al., 2015).

label.value: adult protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2-ellipsoid body tile-ventral gall neuron

value.value: Adult protocerebral bridge 1 glomerulus-ellipsoid body tile-gall neuron that receives its input mainly in protocerebral bridge glomerulus 2 (Wolff et al., 2015). In the ellipsoid body, its output terminals are in the ventrolateral tile of the opposite hemisphere and it projects to the ventral gall (Wolff et al., 2015).

value.value: Dorsal (central) region of the pars intercerebralis of the adult (de Velasco et al., 2007; Ito et al., 2014).

label.value: adult fruitless aSP-g neuron

value.value: Fruitless-expressing neuron with its soma in the adult anterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 13 of these neurons per hemisphere in both males and females (Cachero et al., 2010). They have sexually dimorphic arbors in the lateral protocerebral complex (Cachero et al., 2010; Yu et al., 2010; Kohl et al., 2013) and respond to different odor stimuli in each sex (Kohl et al., 2013).

definition.value: AD1e1 referred to as a fruitless aSP-g neuron in Dolan et al. (2019) and is a synonym for some aSP-g1, aSP-g2 and SLP005 neurons in neuprint (neuprint.janelia.org) hemibrain 1.2.1 notes. Bates (2020) lists two different neuroblasts of origin (DPLal2 and DPLal3) for different aSP-g1 individuals. LHAD1e2 mapped to some aSP-g2 and aSP-g3 neurons in hemibrain 1.2.1 notes.

label.value: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron l2PN

value.value: Adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron that belongs to the ventral hemilineage of neuroblast ALl1 (Bates et al., 2020). Secondary neurons of this type are diverse and fasciculate with several different antennal lobe tracts (Bates et al., 2020).

definition.value: Lin et al. (2012) map PNs to Notch OFF hemilineage; classical lPNs belong to dorsal (l) hemilineage according to Bates et al. (2020), so inferring that dorsal (l) hemilineage is Notch OFF, ventral (l2) is ON - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.
